neutral: When I purchased these, I expected them to be noticeably fake when inspecting up close, but there's a major issue with the pair that I wasn't expecting. If you look at the pictures I attached, there are only two main holes on the medial side of the shoe (the side of the shoe which your big toe rests) while a real pair of Foam RNNRs will have three. It's very noticeable if you're aware of what a real pair looks like. As expected, the holes in the shoes aren't as delicately carved out like a real pair, and the holes on the top side of the shoe aren't nearly as wide as a real pair. I bought a size 40 (US men's 7) and it fits decent. I still give this product 3 stars because I only paid $20 for the pair, so I can't be too disappointed. I mean, they're fakes, what can you expect? On a positive note, the shoes got to me 2 weeks before their expected delivery date. I'd recommend buying a fake pair from a different supplier if you want your pair to appear real.
